  "prompt": "How much did each actor get paid to star in The Avengers?",
  "response": "The salaries of actors for \"The Avengers\" (2012) varied significantly based on their roles, experience, and negotiations. Here are some estimates of what the main cast was paid for their performances:\n\n- **Robert Downey Jr. (Iron Man/Tony Stark)**: Approximately $50 million, which included a combination of salary and a percentage of the box office gross.\n- **Chris Evans (Captain America/Steve Rogers)**: Around $3 million for this film.\n- **Chris Hemsworth (Thor)**: Approximately $3 million as well.\n- **Scarlett Johansson (Black Widow/Natasha Romanoff)**: Estimated to be around $2-3 million.\n- **Mark Ruffalo (Hulk/Bruce Banner)**: Around $2 million.\n- **Jeremy Renner (Hawkeye/Clint Barton)**: Estimated at about $1-2 million.\n- **Samuel L. Jackson (Nick Fury)**: Reported to be in the range of $4-6 million.\n\nIt's important to note that salary figures can often include bonuses based on box office performance, and negotiations can vary widely. Additionally, these figures do not necessarily reflect the actors' earnings for subsequent movies in the Marvel Cinematic Universe.",
